						<summary>

						<p>This records a gift of 90 sheep for a perpetual lamp in the temple to be burnt with the daily supply of an <hi rend="italic">uḻakku</hi> of ghee, by <hi rend="bold">Perumāṉ Appaṉ</hi> a merchant of <hi rend="bold">Kumaramāttāṇḍapuram.</hi> This might be an inscription of <hi rend="bold">Parāntaka I.</hi></p>						

						</summary>
